{
  "skillId":"parallel-perpendicular-notation","atomType":"Cat",
  "theory":{"intro":"Parallel and perpendicular lines use symbols and diagram marks that communicate their relationship at a glance.","facts":["$AB \\parallel CD$ means line $AB$ is **parallel** to line $CD$; the lines remain the same distance apart.","$EF \\perp GH$ means line $EF$ is **perpendicular** to line $GH$; they meet at $90^{\\circ}$.","Matching arrowhead marks identify parallel lines. Different arrowhead counts identify different parallel sets.","A small square at an intersection is a right-angle mark and shows perpendicular lines.","A **transversal** is a line that intersects two or more other lines at different points." ]},
  "practice":{"foundation":[
    {"q":"Write using symbols: line $AB$ is parallel to line $CD$.","a":"$AB \\parallel CD$"},
    {"q":"Write using symbols: line $PQ$ is perpendicular to line $RS$.","a":"$PQ \\perp RS$"},
    {"q":"What relationship is shown by the matching arrow marks?","a":"$AB \\parallel CD$","tikz":"\\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.7]\\draw (-2,1)--(2,1) node[right] {$B$};\\node[left] at (-2,1) {$A$};\\draw (-2,-1)--(2,-1) node[right] {$D$};\\node[left] at (-2,-1) {$C$};\\draw[->] (-0.5,1)--(0.25,1);\\draw[->] (-0.5,-1)--(0.25,-1);\\end{tikzpicture}"},
    {"q":"What relationship is shown by the small square?","a":"$EF \\perp GH$","tikz":"\\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.7]\\draw (-2,0)--(2,0) node[right] {$F$};\\node[left] at (-2,0) {$E$};\\draw (0,-1.5)--(0,1.5) node[above] {$H$};\\node[below] at (0,-1.5) {$G$};\\draw (0,0)--(0.28,0)--(0.28,0.28)--(0,0.28);\\end{tikzpicture}"}
  ],"development":[
    {"q":"Name the line that is parallel to $AB$.","a":"Line $CD$","tikz":"\\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.7]\\draw (-2,1)--(2,1);\\node[left] at (-2,1) {$A$};\\node[right] at (2,1) {$B$};\\draw (-2,-1)--(2,-1);\\node[left] at (-2,-1) {$C$};\\node[right] at (2,-1) {$D$};\\draw[->] (-0.3,1)--(0.35,1);\\draw[->] (-0.3,-1)--(0.35,-1);\\end{tikzpicture}"},
    {"q":"Name a pair of perpendicular lines.","a":"$AC \\perp BD$","tikz":"\\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.7]\\draw (-2,0)--(2,0);\\node[left] at (-2,0) {$A$};\\node[right] at (2,0) {$C$};\\draw (0,-1.5)--(0,1.5);\\node[below] at (0,-1.5) {$B$};\\node[above] at (0,1.5) {$D$};\\draw (0,0)--(0.3,0)--(0.3,0.3)--(0,0.3);\\end{tikzpicture}"},
    {"q":"Line $t$ crosses lines $p$ and $q$ at different points. Name the transversal.","a":"Line $t$","tikz":"\\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.7]\\draw (-2,1)--(2,1) node[right] {$p$};\\draw (-2,-1)--(2,-1) node[right] {$q$};\\draw (-1.2,-1.7)--(0.7,1.7) node[above] {$t$};\\end{tikzpicture}"},
    {"q":"Describe every relationship shown by the diagram marks.","a":"$AB \\parallel CD$ and $EF \\perp AB$","tikz":"\\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.65]\\draw (-2,1)--(2,1);\\node[left] at (-2,1) {$A$};\\node[right] at (2,1) {$B$};\\draw (-2,-1)--(2,-1);\\node[left] at (-2,-1) {$C$};\\node[right] at (2,-1) {$D$};\\draw (0,-1.6)--(0,1.6);\\node[below] at (0,-1.6) {$E$};\\node[above] at (0,1.6) {$F$};\\draw[->] (-0.8,1)--(-0.1,1);\\draw[->] (-0.8,-1)--(-0.1,-1);\\draw (0,1)--(0.28,1)--(0.28,1.28)--(0,1.28);\\end{tikzpicture}"}
